import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['temperature'] = pd.to_numeric(data['temperature'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['temperature'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of hourly temperature in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.boxplot(data['pressure'])
    ax.set_title('What is the average hourly pressure in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Pressure (millibars)')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['wind'] = pd.to_numeric(data['wind'], errors='coerce')

    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed (m/s)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of hourly wind speed in Seattle in 2010?', wrap=True)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
